  "prompt": "What are the most popular online payment methods in Germany?",
  "response": "Here are the most popular online payment methods in Germany:\n\n1. PayPal\n- Widely used and trusted\n- Very popular for online shopping\n- Convenient and secure\n\n2. SEPA Direct Debit (Lastschriftverfahren)\n- Commonly used for recurring payments\n- Directly linked to bank accounts\n- Trusted by many Germans\n\n3. Credit Cards\n- Visa and Mastercard are most common\n- Less preferred compared to other European countries\n- Growing in acceptance\n\n4. Giropay\n- Online banking transfer system\n- Directly connected to German bank accounts\n- Secure and widely used for online transactions\n\n5. Sofort Banking (now Klarna Sofort)\n- Real-time online banking payment\n- Instant bank transfer method\n- Popular for e-commerce\n\n6. Apple Pay and Google Pay\n- Increasing in popularity\n- Mobile payment options\n- Convenient for smartphone users\n\n7. Prepaid and Debit Cards\n- Growing in usage\n- Safer alternative to credit cards\n- Particularly popular among younger users\n\nThese methods reflect Germans' preference for secure, direct, and transparent payment solutions.",
